#X text 512 134 Below we use [drawsymbol] and [drawtext] to draw \, respectively \, a symbol whose field name is 'weasel' and a text whose field name is 'boom'. The boom example uses the -e option so that a single click enables it \, whereas editing 'weasel' requires a double click., f 65;
#X text 511 13 When not in "edit" mode \, you can click and drag vertically on the numbers to change their values. Keyboard entry is also supported \, just click and type. For numbers \, symbols and text you can double click to select and change the values. These values are also readable and writeable via the [set] and [text] objects. Right click gives you properties where you can change values as well., f 65;
#X text 52 449 And here we set "-ne" option to disable selecting the text:;
#X text 42 359 Instead of fixed arguments to set color and position you can specify field names \, for instance 'cat' to set the color here. The "-e" option allows selecting the text with a single click:, f 53;
#X connect 1 0 12 0;
#X connect 2 0 12 0;
