#X text 122 13 - draw numbers \, symbols or text fields in a scalar, f 52;
#X text 194 285 examples:;
#X text 31 95 These objects cause text representations of three types of scalar fields (float \, symbo \, list) to be displayed and edited. By default the text can be editing by double-clicking on the text in run mode. In addition \, the "number" variant allows scrolling the value up and down., f 73;
#X text 30 165 Optional creation arguments (-x \, -xe \, -xr \, -e \, -ne) control how mouse clicks are to be interpreted \, allowing dragging up and down (floats only) or point-and-click text editing. Options -x \, -xe \, -xr disable mouse actions \, either altogether or when in edit or run mode. The -e flag ("edit") allows text editing in either edit or run mode \, activated by a single mouse click. The -xe flag does the opposite \, forbidding editing even when the text is double-clicked in run mode., f 73;
